AGI - Immigration "is a disorderly phenomenon in the hands of traffickers" that must be transformed into a phenomenon "regulated by legal, authorized and defined accesses". The President of the Republic Sergio Mattarella said this in the joint declarations with the Ghanaian counterpart Nana Addo Dankwa Akufo-Addo>.
&nbsp;
"All this makes us think of course, thinking about the presence of Italy so well inserted, integrated and appreciated, of the need to face together, globally, the migration phenomenon", said Mattarella, "is a present phenomenon, of great size that must be converted, from a disordered phenomenon, in the cruel hands of traffickers of human beings, in a regulated phenomenon, from legal access, from regular, authorized interests, concordemente defined. It is an important goal to give space to our young generations, to collaboration", he added, citing his visit tomorrow to the center Don Bosco where workers and cooks are trained who will then work in Italy.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
"I want to reassure President Sergio Mattarella that Ghana will cooperate in the elimination of illegal immigration, in the fight against terrorism, in contrast to the effects of climate change," said Akufo-Addo.
<h2> "Measures for multilateralism"
"It binds us a friendship that is based on so many elements, each of which is sufficient for a solid friendship", Mattarella continued, "one of these elements is the belief that together we have, Ghanaians and Italians, for multilateralism, for a world characterized by dialogue, collaboration, solidarity and not opposition, much more in this period in which there are turbulence in Europe, Africa and the Middle East. The more we are convinced to reaffirm strongly that the perspective for humanity is not another: dialogue and collaboration between countries". "War is the wrong way," the two leaders said.
<div </div
It is necessary to work for a "strengthening of the United Nations. The challenges we face, as humanity, first of all, that of climate, require great international collaboration. They are impossible in opposition," said Mattarella, who expressed "preoccupation" for the Sahel crisis, a zone marked by recent military strikes. "The commitment of Italy against piracy in the Gulf of Guinea remains still, where we participate with a military ship for the safety of navigation freedom," added Mattarella, who, tomorrow, before returning to Italy, will visit the Bettica ship.
<h2>"The Matthias Plan for equal collaboration"</h2>
"The choice of the name of Mattei for the plan that the Italian government has launched is not random and is because Mattei was a friend of Ghana, West Africa and the African continent against colonial exploitation," Mattarella said in greeting the Ghanaian delegation. It is a "even plan to protect local resources" and "this is the objective of the Mattei plan" which "want to be of collaboration according to the needs defined by the various countries of the African continent", added Mattarella.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
The Mattei plan evokes "a protagonist of the friendship between Africa and Europe and the independence of Africa," said Mattarella, who said that with this plan the government has the "will to collaborate on the equal level trying to involve Europe".
&nbsp;

