AGI -&nbsp;"Today in the Work Committee we have incardinated the three bills of oppositions on the short week. I appealed to the majority and government: Listen to us. If it is true that all Europe goes in the direction of the reduction of working time it is necessary that Italy does not arrive for the umpteenth time late. We are ready for a constructive confrontation, but Parliament must strike a blow. From next week we will start the hearing cycle: We will hear the social partners, the enterprises that have already innovated by introducing in agreement with the unions, the world of academy, associations. We want it to become a debate on the model of development and production over time of the digital and ecological revolution". Mr Dem Arturo Scotto, Group leader Pd in the Labour Committee.
&nbsp;
"A short working week is equivalent to minor shifts, lower exhaust gases placed in the atmosphere and less waste of resources, with immediate positive effects on the environment. The reduction of working hours can lead to better physical and mental health by decreasing the risks related to stress and too hectic lifestyles thus increasing employee satisfaction, reducing the costs related to illness and absenteeism with an increase in productivity. With the short week they win all, workers, companies and the economy as a whole," he adds.

